<subSubSection id="2BD4378545162A769D591F591C4E6755" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="88A9C68F98F210BE9121DC23AE36BF40" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0B6C8255C7216951C89E6557D2AFD658" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
So far, this species is known only from its type locality, Drashanskata peshtera Cave (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="97C265C98826BAE16BB9A1689B4318F3" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Distribution of cavernicolous Trichopolydesmidae from the Carpathian-Balkan arch and the Rhodope Mountains." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1097.83916.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/674296" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9B06AAABFC5302FDE60F4A1D3BE17C5A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="336D66147BB5D68432C2DF0372AC2790" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1A0ECCE9558EC42F513594C090109F0B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Originally described as a subspecies, 
<taxonomicName id="2651CD9A9B7FA02A0BE2BDE67DCB2021" authorityName="Antić &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Stoev &amp; Akkari" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Antić &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Stoev &amp; Akkari" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Bacillidesmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bacillidesmus bulgaricus subsp. dentatus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="bulgaricus" subSpecies="dentatus">
<emphasis id="484B88372D7C0F6EA8F0F663639F6BC1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Bacillidesmus bulgaricus dentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="30A4DB33A84B00F7601CE298355FBD6A" author="Strasser, K" journalOrPublisher="Annales Zoologici" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="325 - 385" refId="B54" refString="Strasser, K, 1966a. Ueber Diplopoden Bulgariens. Annales Zoologici 23 (12): 325 - 385" title="Ueber Diplopoden Bulgariens." volume="23" year="1966 a">Strasser (1966a)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out significant differences in the structure of the gonopod between 
<taxonomicName id="2B8A7334865F3115324EF1238EDDE290" authorityName="Strasser" authorityYear="1962" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Bacillidesmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bacillidesmus bulgaricus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bulgaricus">
<emphasis id="B029B230300FF9B88BF0EA8E1C23CB20" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Bacillidesmus bulgaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7B6FF81C887944BDE66D2A63C6DFC00B" authorityName="Antić &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Stoev &amp; Akkari" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Antić &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Stoev &amp; Akkari" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Bacillidesmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bacillidesmus dentatus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentatus">
<emphasis id="64B5CEB14D8BD9C590BA2F937E6A22A7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Bacillidesmus dentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as differences in body size. However, he did not notice the differences in the length and arrangement of metatergal setae between the two taxa. The descriptions of the two new species below, one of which is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="05809D9C965AED33BD67E459414BD463" authorityName="Strasser" authorityYear="1962" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Bacillidesmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bacillidesmus bulgaricus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bulgaricus">
<emphasis id="FCBDD886B60BF3B39CA0614CE2FC63A8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Bacillidesmus bulgaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in body size, habitus and gonopods, and the other one to 
<taxonomicName id="AD87C1ACEEB3B08900C72DFEEE5D14EB" authorityName="Antić &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Stoev &amp; Akkari" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Antić &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Stoev &amp; Akkari" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Bacillidesmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bacillidesmus dentatus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentatus">
<emphasis id="8C56024F9083460E103F68168CB6252C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Bacillidesmus dentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, clearly indicate the presence of two groups of species within this genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CA85872F9C87FD80A024B1DBFD18C736" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
As mentioned above, 
<bibRefCitation id="E312A51C49CB1C995DC476F8E3133BA2" author="Ceuca, T" journalOrPublisher="Seria Biologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B17" refString="Ceuca, T, 1992. Quelques aspects sur la faunistique, l'ecologie et la zoogeographie des diplopodes de la Region Balkanique. Bericht des naturwissenschaftlich-medizinischen Vereins in Innsbruck, Supplementum, 411-429." title="Quelques aspects sur la faunistique, l'ecologie et la zoogeographie des diplopodes de la Region Balkanique. Bericht des naturwissenschaftlich-medizinischen Vereins in Innsbruck, Supplementum, 411 - 429." year="1992">Ceuca (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="612A9D0A9EA4AFD315117FF5C8EFA17B" author="Kime, RD" journalOrPublisher="Pensoft Publishers, Sofia-Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B35" refString="Kime, RD, Enghoff, H, 2011. Atlas of European millipedes (Class Diplopoda). Vol. 1. Pensoft Publishers, Sofia-Moscow" title="Atlas of European millipedes (Class Diplopoda). Vol. 1." year="2011">Kime and Enghoff (2011)</bibRefCitation>
treated this taxon as a separate species, 
<taxonomicName id="D675C0845B124ED4F3A4B0E29FAFAAEF" authorityName="Antić &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Stoev &amp; Akkari" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Antić &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Stoev &amp; Akkari" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Bacillidesmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bacillidesmus dentatus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentatus">
<emphasis id="6BEF52B6531C67E288C89DA2693EA193" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Bacillidesmus dentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, without, however, any formal taxonomic act. For the sake of stability of nomenclature here we formally raise this taxon to the species level and transfer it to the newly established genus as 
<taxonomicName id="21B2FC91645779F2B8B62BA7727E23BF" authorityName="gen. nov., comb. nov." authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Strasser" baseAuthorityYear="1966" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Balkanodesminus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Balkanodesminus dentatus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="dentatus">
<emphasis id="94BCEB0E9A19C784AB9033F5B8135FC8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Balkanodesminus dentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov., comb. nov., stat. nov.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
